    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter updating neovim to 0.10.1 via my package manager, filetypes are not detected correctly anymore.\r\n\r\nInstead, when I start neovim, it will show the following error message in the minibuffer:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError detected while processing BufReadPost Autocommands for \"*\":\r\nError executing lua callback: .../share/nvim/lazy/LazyVim/lua/lazyvim/config/autocmds.lua:130:\r\nattempt to compare nil with number\r\nstack traceback:\r\n        .../share/nvim/lazy/LazyVim/lua/lazyvim/config/autocmds.lua:130: in function 'ft'\r\n        vim/filetype.lua:2368: in function 'dispatch'\r\n        vim/filetype.lua:2535: in function 'match'\r\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua:14: in function </usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.\r\nlua:10>\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I press `Enter`, the file will be opened but without any highlighting, plus the filetype in the info bar always says `unix`.\r\n\r\nI checked the mentioned files at the named lines, but my knowledge of those nvim internal things is non-existing.\r\n\r\nI did not make any changes to my neovim config since the update.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUnclear. Tried with the `minimal.lua` conf file, but nearly had to include my whole `init.lua` to reproduce the error.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFiletypes should be detected automatically as regular.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.1 Build type: None LuaJIT 2.1.1720049189\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nVoid Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.17.2 -pgo +ime +graphemes -assertions\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nxbps-install -Su neovim",
