            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@Brikkel, I had the exact same issue, seems this workaround does the job.\r\nIn one of your nvim config files add\r\n\r\n`vim.g.bigfile_size=1024*1024*1 -- 1M`\r\n\r\nFor context:\r\n- ArchLinux\r\n- nvim v0.10.1\r\n- blank LazyVim configuration in \"Structured setup\" (conf files split in directories), following https://lazy.folke.io/installation\r\n- enabled plugins : catppuccin (theme), LazyVim and Telescope\r\n\r\nI added the above line in the .config/nvim/lua/config/lazy.lua\r\n\r\nHope this helps ! (it doesn't solve the root cause however)\r\n\r\n",
